[
    {
        "content": "<p>Folks in CT love to stick \"co\" on the front of words. Can I assume there is some overarching concept?</p>",
        "id": 197431276,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Geisler",
        "timestamp": 1589384476
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yep, it has a technical meaning, \"turn the arrows round\". A <em>cothing</em> in the category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span> always means the same as a <em>thing</em> in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>C</mi><mrow><mi>o</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C^{op}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.664392em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>",
        "id": 197431613,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1589384583
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes! Dualisation! <span aria-label=\"tada\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f389\" role=\"img\" title=\"tada\">:tada:</span></p>",
        "id": 197431709,
        "sender_full_name": "[Mod] Morgan Rogers",
        "timestamp": 1589384600
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>MIND BLOWN!!!</p>",
        "id": 197431798,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Geisler",
        "timestamp": 1589384631
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>eg. a comonoid in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Set</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">t</span></span></span></span> is by definition the same thing as a monoid in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi><mi>e</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mrow><mi>o</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Set^{op}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">e</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">t</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.664392em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>",
        "id": 197431805,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1589384636
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This would be where I make the joke that a comathematician is a machine that turns cotheorems into ffee...</p>",
        "id": 197432327,
        "sender_full_name": "[Mod] Morgan Rogers",
        "timestamp": 1589384793
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Part of the general approach of category theorists is a belief that if <em>things</em> are interesting, then most likely <em>cothings</em> are probably interesting too (but cothings can potentially be very different to things)</p>",
        "id": 197432720,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1589384887
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I love combinatorics!</p>",
        "id": 197432920,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Geisler",
        "timestamp": 1589384974
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For names like that I personally like the convention of replacing the co- with a phonetically pleasing vowel. So I might call the study of finite decompositions of things umbinatorics, if that were to need a name, but perhaps cocombinatorics would be the standard construction.</p>",
        "id": 197433338,
        "sender_full_name": "[Mod] Morgan Rogers",
        "timestamp": 1589385153
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Going from learning the concept of dualisation to make your first dualisation joke in about 3 minutes, I think that's a new world record</p>",
        "id": 197433343,
        "sender_full_name": "Jules Hedges",
        "timestamp": 1589385154
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Too bad I'm a better comedian than mathematician. ;)</p>",
        "id": 197434095,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Geisler",
        "timestamp": 1589385433
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The median isn't defined in terms of categories, so I don't think you can dualize it...</p>",
        "id": 197435192,
        "sender_full_name": "Oscar Cunningham",
        "timestamp": 1589385874
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Going further off-topic, it's interesting to read about the difference between a <a href=\"https://newyorkcomedy.wordpress.com/2013/07/02/comic-vs-comedian-whats-the-difference/\">comedian and a comic</a>.</p>",
        "id": 197435569,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1589386028
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I have a difficulty here, let's say I don't do duality or discrete, or maybe I just want something deeper.</p>",
        "id": 197440261,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Geisler",
        "timestamp": 1589387993
    }
]